{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Uhw7e7ZkKBT1DJZH7BGWt7","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my final report:\n\n## Summary: Workflow Run Error Handling and Display in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how workflow run errors are currently handled and displayed:\n\n### 1. **Run Domain Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\nThe `Run` struct has these key fields for error handling:\n- **`ErrorMessage string`** (line 49) - Stores the error/failure message\n- **`State RunState`** - One of: `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n- **`StepExecutions []*StepExecution`** - Tracks each step execution with result status\n- **`ActiveSteps []string`** - Current executing steps\n\nThe `Run` type provides methods:\n- **`Complete(state RunState)`** (lines 113-116) - Marks run as complete with given state\n- **`Fail(msg string)`** (lines 118-122) - Sets state to `RunStateFailed` and stores error message\n\n### 2. **Step Failure Recording** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\nWhen a step fails:\n- **`RecordStepStart(stepName string)`** (lines 72-78) - Records step start with timestamp\n- **`RecordStepComplete(stepName, result string)`** (lines 80-96) - Stores step result and completion time\n  - Result can be \"success\", \"fail\", \"error\", or custom result names\n  - Removes from active steps list when complete\n\n### 3. **Error/Failure Fields Storage** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n\nThe SQLite store persists error information:\n- **`error_message TEXT`** column (line 78) - Stores error details\n- **`state TEXT`** column - Stores the run state (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- **Error truncation** (lines 489-499) - Error messages capped at 1000 characters to prevent database bloat\n  - Full error details remain in step logs\n\n**StepExecution table** captures:\n- `step_name`, `result`, `started_at`, `completed_at`, `logs`, `git_ref`\n\n### 4. **CLI Display of Run Status/Errors** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\n**`cmdStatus` function** (lines 218-255):\n- Displays run state, active steps, and **error message** (lines 248-250)\n- Shows step execution history with results\n\n**`cmdList` function** (lines 257-345):\n- Lists runs with error messages truncated to 60 characters (lines 336-342)\n- Shows state, workflow, container ID, and error\n\n**`cmdPoll` function** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`):\n- **Single run polling** (lines 27-86): Prints run state changes and step events\n  - Displays error message on failed/cancelled states (lines 68-70)\n- **Multi-run polling** (lines 99-155): Compact status summary\n\n### 5. **RunStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`)\n\nThe `RunStore` interface (lines 10-20) defines:\n- `CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run)` - Persist new run\n- `GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string)` - Retrieve run (includes error_message)\n- `UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run)` - Update run state/errors\n- `ListRunsFiltered(ctx context.Context, filter domain.RunListFilter)` - Query runs by state\n\n### 6. **gRPC Response Schema** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)\n\n**GetStatusResponse** (lines 41-53):\n- `error_message` field (line 47) - Transmitted to clients\n- `state` - Run state (succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- Step execution details\n\n**RunSummary** (lines 106-116):\n- Includes `error_message` for list operations\n\n**GetStatus implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 425-477):\n- Populates `ErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage` in response\n- Returns current and completed step executions\n\n### 7. **Agent/Container Error Reporting**\n\n**Protocol Status Messages** (`/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`):\n- `MsgRunCompleted` (line 15) - Final run result sent by container\n- `MsgError` (line 19) - Errors from agent steps\n- `MsgStepCompleted` with result field captures pass/fail\n\n**Agent Runner** (`/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`):\n- On run error (lines 97-103): Logs error, writes to unified log, calls `statusWriter.Error()` and `statusWriter.RunCompleted(\"failed\")`\n- Step execution errors stop the workflow and set run state to failed\n- Full error details logged in step output files\n\n### 8. **Host Workflow Error Handling** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`)\n\n**Host executor** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`):\n- Script execution failure (lines 140-147): Returns \"fail\" result if exit code non-zero\n- Workflow steps that fail (line 220): Return \"fail\" result\n- All errors propagated to engine which stops the workflow\n\n**Runner finalization** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` lines 143-155):\n- On run error: Calls `hostRun.Fail(runErr.Error())` to record error message\n- Otherwise: Calls `hostRun.Complete(result.State)`\n\n### 9. **Web API Error Display** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\n\n**apiRun structure** (lines 476-491):\n- `ErrorMessage` field (line 486) included in JSON responses\n\n### 10. **Engine Error Handling** (`/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`)\n\nStep execution errors (lines 178-184):\n- If step executor returns error: Records \"error\" result, sets run to failed, returns error\n- If undeclared result: Records result, sets to failed, returns error\n- If wiring error: Sets to failed if not handled by collect\n\n### 11. **Container Failure Scenarios** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\nErrors are captured in background tracking:\n- **Image build failure** (line 150): `run.Fail(\"failed to ensure image: ...\")`\n- **Container start failure** (line 170): `run.Fail(\"failed to start container: ...\")`\n- **Exit code non-zero** (line 347): `run.Fail(\"container exited with code ...\")`\n- **Daemon restart while running** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` line 457): `run.Fail(\"daemon restarted while run was active\")`\n\n---\n\n## Key File Paths\n\n**Domain & Storage:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run struct and Fail() method\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore interface\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - SQLite implementation with error truncation\n\n**Execution & Error Reporting:**\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow engine error handling\n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - Host workflow step execution\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - Host runner error finalization\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - Container agent error reporting\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - Background tracking and error persistence\n\n**User-Facing Display:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - cmdStatus() and cmdList() display errors\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` - Poll display of error messages\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - REST API JSON serialization\n\n**Protocol & API:**\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` - Error and RunCompleted message types\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC schema with error_message fields"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5e3e53f5ec889383 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 80564\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 47948</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b83d887-9f3b-4385-8c16-91cb9c40f66f","uuid":"e995d6f6-e4c9-49ed-b263-e1e081588854","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go codebase to understand how workflow run errors are currently handled and displayed. I need to find:\n\n1. The Run domain type - how errors/failures are stored (look in internal/domain/)\n2. How step failures are recorded - what happens when a step fails\n3. How run status/errors are displayed to users (CLI output, gRPC responses)\n4. The RunStore interface and implementations - how run state is persisted\n5. Any existing \"error\" or \"failure\" fields on the Run type\n\nSearch thoroughly across:\n- internal/domain/ for Run, Step, Result types\n- internal/ports/ for store interfaces\n- internal/adapters/ for store implementations (especially SQLite)\n- cmd/cloche/ for CLI display of run status/errors\n- internal/host/ for host workflow executor error handling\n- Look for how the agent reports step failures back\n\nBe very thorough - read the key files fully.","agentId":"a5e3e53f5ec889383","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my final report:\n\n## Summary: Workflow Run Error Handling and Display in Cloche\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how workflow run errors are currently handled and displayed:\n\n### 1. **Run Domain Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\nThe `Run` struct has these key fields for error handling:\n- **`ErrorMessage string`** (line 49) - Stores the error/failure message\n- **`State RunState`** - One of: `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n- **`StepExecutions []*StepExecution`** - Tracks each step execution with result status\n- **`ActiveSteps []string`** - Current executing steps\n\nThe `Run` type provides methods:\n- **`Complete(state RunState)`** (lines 113-116) - Marks run as complete with given state\n- **`Fail(msg string)`** (lines 118-122) - Sets state to `RunStateFailed` and stores error message\n\n### 2. **Step Failure Recording** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`)\n\nWhen a step fails:\n- **`RecordStepStart(stepName string)`** (lines 72-78) - Records step start with timestamp\n- **`RecordStepComplete(stepName, result string)`** (lines 80-96) - Stores step result and completion time\n  - Result can be \"success\", \"fail\", \"error\", or custom result names\n  - Removes from active steps list when complete\n\n### 3. **Error/Failure Fields Storage** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n\nThe SQLite store persists error information:\n- **`error_message TEXT`** column (line 78) - Stores error details\n- **`state TEXT`** column - Stores the run state (pending/running/succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- **Error truncation** (lines 489-499) - Error messages capped at 1000 characters to prevent database bloat\n  - Full error details remain in step logs\n\n**StepExecution table** captures:\n- `step_name`, `result`, `started_at`, `completed_at`, `logs`, `git_ref`\n\n### 4. **CLI Display of Run Status/Errors** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\n**`cmdStatus` function** (lines 218-255):\n- Displays run state, active steps, and **error message** (lines 248-250)\n- Shows step execution history with results\n\n**`cmdList` function** (lines 257-345):\n- Lists runs with error messages truncated to 60 characters (lines 336-342)\n- Shows state, workflow, container ID, and error\n\n**`cmdPoll` function** (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go`):\n- **Single run polling** (lines 27-86): Prints run state changes and step events\n  - Displays error message on failed/cancelled states (lines 68-70)\n- **Multi-run polling** (lines 99-155): Compact status summary\n\n### 5. **RunStore Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`)\n\nThe `RunStore` interface (lines 10-20) defines:\n- `CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run)` - Persist new run\n- `GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string)` - Retrieve run (includes error_message)\n- `UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run)` - Update run state/errors\n- `ListRunsFiltered(ctx context.Context, filter domain.RunListFilter)` - Query runs by state\n\n### 6. **gRPC Response Schema** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`)\n\n**GetStatusResponse** (lines 41-53):\n- `error_message` field (line 47) - Transmitted to clients\n- `state` - Run state (succeeded/failed/cancelled)\n- Step execution details\n\n**RunSummary** (lines 106-116):\n- Includes `error_message` for list operations\n\n**GetStatus implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 425-477):\n- Populates `ErrorMessage: run.ErrorMessage` in response\n- Returns current and completed step executions\n\n### 7. **Agent/Container Error Reporting**\n\n**Protocol Status Messages** (`/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`):\n- `MsgRunCompleted` (line 15) - Final run result sent by container\n- `MsgError` (line 19) - Errors from agent steps\n- `MsgStepCompleted` with result field captures pass/fail\n\n**Agent Runner** (`/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`):\n- On run error (lines 97-103): Logs error, writes to unified log, calls `statusWriter.Error()` and `statusWriter.RunCompleted(\"failed\")`\n- Step execution errors stop the workflow and set run state to failed\n- Full error details logged in step output files\n\n### 8. **Host Workflow Error Handling** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`)\n\n**Host executor** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`):\n- Script execution failure (lines 140-147): Returns \"fail\" result if exit code non-zero\n- Workflow steps that fail (line 220): Return \"fail\" result\n- All errors propagated to engine which stops the workflow\n\n**Runner finalization** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` lines 143-155):\n- On run error: Calls `hostRun.Fail(runErr.Error())` to record error message\n- Otherwise: Calls `hostRun.Complete(result.State)`\n\n### 9. **Web API Error Display** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`)\n\n**apiRun structure** (lines 476-491):\n- `ErrorMessage` field (line 486) included in JSON responses\n\n### 10. **Engine Error Handling** (`/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`)\n\nStep execution errors (lines 178-184):\n- If step executor returns error: Records \"error\" result, sets run to failed, returns error\n- If undeclared result: Records result, sets to failed, returns error\n- If wiring error: Sets to failed if not handled by collect\n\n### 11. **Container Failure Scenarios** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n\nErrors are captured in background tracking:\n- **Image build failure