{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011RgDa2KnJMDwshcGZ4kQS9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Problem:** When a container workflow run failed, the error message was not captured, making it hard to diagnose failures without reading full logs.\n\n**Changes:**\n\n1. **`internal/agent/runner.go`** - When the engine returns an error, the agent now extracts the failed step name from `run.StepExecutions` (looking for steps with \"error\" or \"fail\" result) and includes it in the `MsgError` status message sent to the daemon.\n\n2. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** - The server's `trackRun` method now:\n   - Handles `MsgError` protocol messages (previously ignored) and captures the error text\n   - Uses the captured error message when finalizing failed runs: calls `run.Fail(reportedError)` instead of `run.Complete(RunStateFailed)`, which sets the `ErrorMessage` field on the run\n\n3. **Tests added:**\n   - `TestEngine_StepErrorIncludesStepName` - Verifies the engine error contains the step name and original error\n   - `TestRunner_FailedStepReportsErrorWithStepName` - Verifies the agent runner handles abort paths\n   - `TestRunner_StepExecutionErrorReportsErrorWithStepName` - Verifies `MsgError` includes step name on execution errors\n   - `TestServer_RunWorkflow_FailedRunCapturesErrorMessage` - End-to-end test verifying the error message is persisted on the run and visible via `GetStatus`\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":258,"cache_read_input_tokens":91443,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":258},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3b83d887-9f3b-4385-8c16-91cb9c40f66f","uuid":"1158d1ff-d7b4-489f-8a1d-271665369dc5"}
